# Data Encryption Standards

All PHI and sensitive configuration must be encrypted at rest and protected during transport.

## At Rest
- Use WebCrypto AES-GCM with unique IVs per record.
- Store encrypted payloads in IndexedDB; store only encrypted blobs in `chrome.storage.*`.
- Never persist raw keys alongside ciphertext; derive keys from a secure local key source and rotate on schema version changes.
- Include schema version and algorithm metadata with encrypted records for future migrations.

## In Transit
- Only send de-identified data to external AI providers.
- Use HTTPS-only endpoints; verify OAuth scopes and audiences.

## Key Management
- Scope keys per profile and per data domain when feasible (e.g., MPR vs redaction map).
- Provide a safe re-key path for schema upgrades; keep migrations idempotent.

## Verification
- Add tests that assert no plaintext PHI is written to storage or logs.
- Run encryption/decryption round-trip tests for all PHI-bearing models.
